WEBVTT

00:09.259 --> 00:10.969
It was a polio year,

00:11.052 --> 00:13.096
and I was 6 years old,

00:13.179 --> 00:14.723
and my mother
decides to teach me

00:14.806 --> 00:17.100
every card and board game
known to man.

00:17.183 --> 00:20.478
Gin rummy, blackjack,
poker, bridge.

00:20.562 --> 00:22.439
Eventually,
we landed on Monopoly.

00:22.522 --> 00:25.525
Now, Monopoly takes strategy,

00:25.608 --> 00:27.902
and skill,
like those other games,

00:27.986 --> 00:30.572
but it also throws in
an element of chance.

00:30.655 --> 00:33.199
So, no matter how good
you are at the game,

00:33.283 --> 00:34.909
the bad breaks come,

00:34.993 --> 00:36.661
and they knock you on your ass.

00:36.745 --> 00:39.998
And, well, lately,
we've had a few of those.

00:40.081 --> 00:42.041
Frank
"Banker's up your ass.

00:42.125 --> 00:43.418
Pay three million bucks."

00:43.501 --> 00:45.336
"Coach falls off bike.

00:45.420 --> 00:47.380
Go back 10 spaces."

00:47.464 --> 00:49.799
"Mother diagnosed
with metastatic cancer.

00:49.883 --> 00:52.218
Stare into abyss."

00:52.302 --> 00:55.430
Yeah.
So, it turns out my mother
wasn't losing her marbles.

00:55.513 --> 00:59.726
It was cancer giving
her strokes. Anyway...

00:59.809 --> 01:03.480
Thing about luck is,
it cuts both ways.

01:03.563 --> 01:06.983
You hold on long enough,
and you stay in the game.

01:07.984 --> 01:09.444
It's the law of big numbers.

01:10.361 --> 01:11.738
Eventually...

01:12.447 --> 01:13.907
it goes your way.

01:13.990 --> 01:17.994
"Win NBA Championship.
Find happiness
and peace you seek."

01:20.038 --> 01:21.873
My point is...

01:21.956 --> 01:23.291
I'm fucking due.

