06:52.537 --> 06:54.205
Could you please not help me?

06:54.288 --> 06:55.373
Just...

06:56.791 --> 06:58.042
Yes, you're almost there.

06:58.126 --> 07:00.670
You just have to ke-- keep
pulling the lace through the--

07:00.753 --> 07:02.130
-Goddamn it!

07:04.215 --> 07:06.968
Been working on your
shooting touch?

07:07.051 --> 07:08.970
I got a coach around
here somewhere.

07:10.346 --> 07:11.430
This a bad time?

07:11.514 --> 07:13.850
No. Stay.

07:13.933 --> 07:15.810
We need the break.

07:15.893 --> 07:16.936
I'm sorry.

07:20.898 --> 07:23.943
She needs a break from me.
You caught me in a mood.

07:24.026 --> 07:27.029
Hm, you must have seen
the game last night.

07:27.113 --> 07:28.614
They pulled it out.

07:28.698 --> 07:29.866
Yeah,

07:29.949 --> 07:32.451
and the guys said that
should've been an easy one.

07:34.620 --> 07:36.497
What else
are the guys saying?

07:36.581 --> 07:38.666
That we're being out-coached.

07:38.749 --> 07:41.878
And this keeps up,
we're gonna blow our shot.

07:43.379 --> 07:45.923
They've seen enough.

07:46.007 --> 07:48.885
I need to make
a run this season, Jack.

07:50.970 --> 07:53.681
Then bet on me.

07:53.764 --> 07:56.684
I know I don't look like
your sure thing, but...

07:57.476 --> 07:59.187
I'm your guy.

08:00.188 --> 08:02.231
I'm comin' back.

08:02.315 --> 08:04.817
-If Westhead keeps slip--
-Give him the road trip.

08:06.861 --> 08:09.530
Indiana, Detroit.

08:09.614 --> 08:12.033
Boston. Now, there's a test.

08:12.116 --> 08:13.534
That's the best team
in the league.

08:13.618 --> 08:16.329
Closest thing to playoff-
level competition.

08:16.412 --> 08:17.914
And it's the Garden.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.957
You know what the Garden's like.
It's a beast.

08:20.041 --> 08:23.169
If Paul can beat them
in the Garden,

08:23.252 --> 08:25.880
then he can mind the store
until the doctors clear me

08:25.963 --> 08:28.466
to come back. One month.

08:28.549 --> 08:30.593
Two months tops.

08:32.178 --> 08:34.972
Look at you.

08:39.268 --> 08:41.646
Boston.

08:41.729 --> 08:43.731
Jack McKinney
You're under a microscope.

08:43.814 --> 08:45.024
West is circling like a vulture

08:45.107 --> 08:46.901
and already looking
to replace us.

08:46.984 --> 08:49.528
Christ.
I'm doing my best, Jack.

08:49.612 --> 08:51.113
Mc
I need better than that.

08:51.197 --> 08:53.449
I came back from
the dead for this.

08:53.533 --> 08:56.410
-For this, Paul.
-I know.

08:56.494 --> 08:58.120
I should be gone. I'm not.

08:58.204 --> 09:00.790
I'm here, and I'll be
back on that sideline

09:00.873 --> 09:02.375
if it kills me again.

09:02.458 --> 09:05.461
But not if you can't keep
this thing together for me.

09:05.544 --> 09:07.964
Paul
I won't let you down, Jack.

09:15.554 --> 09:18.808
I'm just glad a lifetime of this
shit is good for something.

09:18.891 --> 09:21.727
I would, uh...

09:21.811 --> 09:24.230
What do you...
What do you think

09:24.313 --> 09:26.941
about if we make this
something more official?

09:27.024 --> 09:30.444
-This thing, you and me?
-Uh...

09:30.528 --> 09:32.989
I'm a married man.

09:33.072 --> 09:35.700
I'm flailing out there,
Pat.

09:36.867 --> 09:39.203
I know it.

09:39.287 --> 09:42.832
Everybody knows it.
I need an assistant.

09:42.915 --> 09:44.458
And not like this,
you know, ad hoc

09:44.542 --> 09:46.794
passing notes down
from the press box.

09:46.877 --> 09:49.005
I need somebody with me.

09:50.089 --> 09:52.008
On the bench.

09:52.091 --> 09:53.759
For this trip.

09:53.843 --> 09:56.721
-But, assistant coach?
-Yeah, I mean, why not?

09:57.596 --> 10:00.016
You're fucking
great at it.

10:00.099 --> 10:02.351
Look, no offense
to your broadcasting career,

10:02.435 --> 10:04.061
but Chick is not
going to miss you.

10:04.145 --> 10:07.064
-Is he? I will.
-No.

10:07.148 --> 10:10.359
I really will.
So, so, what do you say?

10:11.944 --> 10:13.529
Please.

10:17.783 --> 10:18.993
What about Jack?

10:19.076 --> 10:21.412
What happens when
he comes back? I mean,

10:21.495 --> 10:23.080
if I quit my job for this,

10:23.164 --> 10:25.875
I can't go back
to wandering the beach.
I-I'll fucking croak.

10:25.958 --> 10:28.044
We'll keep you-- He'll...

10:28.127 --> 10:30.046
He'll keep you on.

10:30.838 --> 10:32.965
-Yeah?
-Absolutely.

10:42.767 --> 10:44.894
Fuck it! What? Fuck it.

10:44.977 --> 10:46.562
-Fuck it yes?

10:46.645 --> 10:48.397
Shit, fuck it. Yeah, I'm in.

10:48.481 --> 10:50.608
-Yes!
-Let's kick some ass.

10:50.691 --> 10:52.651
This is-- Let's kick--
Yeah, absolutely.

10:52.735 --> 10:54.570
I'm gonna shake your hand,
and I'm gonna hug you.

10:54.653 --> 10:57.239
Dick Enberg
And Johnson's putting
on a show tonight,

10:57.323 --> 11:01.035
a tremendous athlete with
a talented team behind him.

11:01.118 --> 11:03.120
But, man for man, Larry Bird

11:03.204 --> 11:05.081
has got to be
the more skilled player.

11:05.164 --> 11:06.916
This kid from
Indiana farm country,

11:06.999 --> 11:09.585
he's not thinking about
the shot in front of him.

11:09.668 --> 11:11.545
He's thinking about the game.

11:11.629 --> 11:14.632
He must see the whole
court in his head.

11:17.176 --> 11:19.345
I want to thank my family.
I want to thank Coach

11:19.428 --> 11:22.264
for drawing up a game plan
and Indiana State for--

11:22.348 --> 11:24.600
-They played a hell of a game.

11:24.683 --> 11:28.270
Mm, all the fans
that done came out.

11:28.354 --> 11:31.565
-I just wanna say thank--

11:31.649 --> 11:34.902
Gonna torch that
smiley ass in Boston, punk.

11:36.278 --> 11:38.239
You wish, motherfucker.

11:43.702 --> 11:46.330
Here you go, sir. Time to take
the Magic Show on the road.

11:46.414 --> 11:49.417
Three cities, five nights,

11:49.500 --> 11:52.128
two in Michigan.
Gonna catch the fam,

11:52.211 --> 11:54.964
see Cook,
then it's off to Boston.

11:55.047 --> 11:57.133
Hey, Magic! Magic! Hey, Magic!

11:57.216 --> 12:00.177
First shot at Larry Bird
as a pro. You excited?

12:00.261 --> 12:03.013
Larry on this trip?
Guess I must've forgot.

12:03.097 --> 12:04.557
I got my mind
on Detroit.

12:04.640 --> 12:07.351
Whole team be coming by
the Johnson family house

12:07.435 --> 12:08.644
for Christmas dinner.

12:08.727 --> 12:10.312
We'll bring y'all doggie bag.

12:10.396 --> 12:12.022
I know it's a big rematch.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.691
-Any nerves?
-Nerves?

12:13.774 --> 12:15.317
Nah, it's just
another game, man.

12:15.401 --> 12:17.236
I'm sure you've heard
the numbers Larry put on Philly.

12:17.319 --> 12:19.280
I mean, they're
already talking MVP.

12:19.363 --> 12:21.657
Yeah? Hadn't heard.

12:21.740 --> 12:23.784
Excuse me, fellas.
Got a flight to catch.

12:23.868 --> 12:26.078
Do you think
he's Rookie of the Year?

12:28.706 --> 12:30.791
You know, y'all keep
asking me about him.

12:30.875 --> 12:34.128
Larry took me
too light last time.
And how that work out?

12:34.211 --> 12:36.672
-Dude best be worryin' about me.
-That's my quote.

12:36.755 --> 12:38.883
-So you out for blood this time?
-Will he be crying
into another towel...

12:38.966 --> 12:40.926
-Gentlemen!
-...after this game or what?

12:41.010 --> 12:43.095
That's enough.
We have a flight.

12:43.179 --> 12:45.264
No more questions, Cap.

12:45.347 --> 12:46.891
I fucked up, didn't I?

12:52.271 --> 12:54.273
Hey, Earvin.

12:54.356 --> 12:56.650
There you go.
First road trip?

12:56.734 --> 12:57.818
-Mm-hmm.
-Alright. You know,

12:57.902 --> 12:59.445
there are gonna be
a lot of groupies out there.

12:59.528 --> 13:01.238
You just wanna... wrap it up,

13:01.322 --> 13:02.448
you know what I'm saying?

13:02.531 --> 13:05.034
-We'll see.
-Alright? Trust me.

13:05.117 --> 13:07.119
-Hey, kid.
-Hey, Chick.

13:07.203 --> 13:08.496
I'm telling you,
Patricia, you're making

13:08.579 --> 13:10.664
a big mistake with this
whole coaching business.

13:10.748 --> 13:12.791
I think your true calling
is in herding cats.

13:12.875 --> 13:15.377
-Ha, ha. Thanks, Chick.

13:15.461 --> 13:16.837
I'm gonna miss him.

13:16.921 --> 13:19.131
-Take this, please. Thank you.
-Please! Just listen! Pat!

13:19.215 --> 13:20.508
-Jerry?
-You tell the Gestapo here--

13:20.591 --> 13:21.800
This man does
not have a ticket.

13:21.884 --> 13:23.719
-Jerry, what are you--
-Jerry West. Right on there.

13:23.802 --> 13:25.137
Thank you very
much for your help.

13:25.221 --> 13:27.306
-God, Jesus fuckin' Christ.
-What is this? What's going on?

13:27.389 --> 13:28.682
Well, it's
a last-minute thing.

13:28.766 --> 13:30.893
I'm doing a little,
uh, consulting,

13:30.976 --> 13:32.811
working on a, uh,
scouting problem for Buss.

13:32.895 --> 13:34.522
Well, the office didn't tell me
you were coming. I...

13:34.605 --> 13:36.690
Well, it must be right there.
It's a little, you know,

13:36.774 --> 13:38.359
mum's the word.
Don't wanna
ruffle any feathers.

13:38.442 --> 13:40.736
So, which seat am I in, Pat?
Sort this out, okay?

13:40.819 --> 13:42.780
-Don't leave me hanging.
Thank you for your help.
-Uh...

13:42.863 --> 13:44.698
-Next to Chick here?
-Uh,

13:44.782 --> 13:46.700
well, no, you can
have my seat.

13:46.784 --> 13:49.745
-Yeah? Where's that?
-That's, uh,
right by the toilet.

13:49.828 --> 13:53.499
-Over there. Coach.
-Down here in
the clown section, huh?

13:55.000 --> 13:57.503
Hey, uh, Paul?

13:57.586 --> 14:00.506
Any clue why West is here?
He says he's on a scout.

14:03.092 --> 14:05.511
Are we making any
moves on personnel?

14:08.806 --> 14:11.559
I mean, if we drop this one
to Indiana, we might have to.

14:19.149 --> 14:21.026
Well, you weren't wrong
about your mother.

14:21.110 --> 14:23.279
She's one hell of an accountant.
Even her mistakes are good.

14:23.362 --> 14:25.573
-How's that, Claire?
-Claire Three words.

14:25.656 --> 14:29.243
Depreciation of assets.

14:29.326 --> 14:30.869
We're gonna need
some more words.

14:30.953 --> 14:32.246
Okay. It's like this.

14:32.329 --> 14:34.748
Every team pays
their players as employees,

14:34.832 --> 14:37.251
but, according to the IRS,
they're also assets.

14:37.334 --> 14:40.129
Which means we should be able
to deduct their total value

14:40.212 --> 14:41.630
in depreciation over time.

14:41.714 --> 14:44.091
-Yeah, their salaries.
-No, we already write off
their salaries.

14:44.174 --> 14:45.634
That's just what they earn.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.636
The total value,
that's more murky.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.555
That's what they're worth.
Without these players,

14:49.638 --> 14:51.974
we don't have a team.
So, in that sense,

14:52.057 --> 14:53.809
their total value
to the business

14:53.892 --> 14:57.104
must be the total value
of the business.

14:57.187 --> 14:58.397
Everything you paid for it.

14:58.480 --> 15:01.567
-No.
-No fucking way. Impossible.

15:01.650 --> 15:03.027
Yet strangely legal,

15:03.110 --> 15:05.571
and maybe just enough
to save your ass.

15:05.654 --> 15:09.283
If we can keep winning
and make a playoff run,

15:09.366 --> 15:11.535
which, I guess you know,
is a pretty big if.

15:14.371 --> 15:15.748
Lakers here in Indiana

15:15.831 --> 15:17.875
on the first of a three-game
holiday season road trip

15:17.958 --> 15:19.960
against a struggling
Pacers team.

15:20.044 --> 15:22.087
This should be as sure
a thing as a candy cane

15:22.171 --> 15:24.548
in your stocking
Christmas morning.

15:28.093 --> 15:29.637
Earvin
Yeah, they got us there, gang.

15:29.720 --> 15:31.472
But we gonna get
'em the next one.

15:31.555 --> 15:35.100
We headin' to D-Town,
and we ain't losing in D-Town.

15:36.810 --> 15:38.687
You feel me? Go home,

15:38.771 --> 15:40.773
get me some of my
mama's home cooking.

15:40.856 --> 15:45.027
-And we gonna be a'ight.

15:45.110 --> 15:48.322
Hey! Magic Man! Sign these?

15:48.405 --> 15:51.575
-Larry's gonna eat your lunch.

15:51.659 --> 15:52.910
Hey, put the tits away.

15:52.993 --> 15:56.330
We'll see.
You tune in and find out.

15:56.413 --> 15:59.500
So, should we be nagging Coach
to give you some more minutes?

15:59.583 --> 16:02.169
Spencer
Man, what I say? Huh?
Maybe if the coach put me in

16:02.252 --> 16:04.546
outside of garbage time,
gave me a real run,

16:04.630 --> 16:07.341
they wouldn't be gettin' beat
in the paint. That's for sure.

16:07.424 --> 16:09.760
-But that ain't on me.

16:10.928 --> 16:12.805
You can ask the
Nutty Professor though.

16:12.888 --> 16:14.181
Shit.

16:15.015 --> 16:16.266
You fuckin' kidding me?

16:22.815 --> 16:23.899
Listen to me.

16:23.982 --> 16:25.693
That crossed
a fucking line, alright?

16:25.776 --> 16:26.902
He's been pushing you.
Alright?

16:26.985 --> 16:28.404
The other guys see you
walk away from this,

16:28.487 --> 16:30.739
-you're gonna be
a substitute forever.
-It's my fault.

16:30.823 --> 16:34.034
I heard something
a few weeks ago.

16:34.118 --> 16:37.996
I overreacted.
I benched him.

16:38.080 --> 16:41.083
it spiraled,
and now it's public.

16:41.166 --> 16:43.961
-But it's my fault.
-Alright, so?

16:44.044 --> 16:45.796
Talk to him.

16:45.879 --> 16:47.923
Tell him. Tell Spencer.

16:48.006 --> 16:49.967
-Just apologize.
-That's your...

16:50.050 --> 16:51.885
That's your grand advice?

16:51.969 --> 16:53.762
They already treat me
like a pushover.

16:53.846 --> 16:56.223
These aren't fucking
college kids.

16:56.306 --> 16:58.016
Paul, these are men. Okay?

16:58.100 --> 17:02.062
They will respect you
if you treat them with respect.

17:02.146 --> 17:05.524
-Let him through,
let him through.

17:07.818 --> 17:10.946
I appreciate the insight, Pat.

17:27.337 --> 17:28.630
Shit.

17:33.886 --> 17:35.179
Jerry
Well...

17:36.555 --> 17:38.182
Oh-for-one on the road trip.

17:38.265 --> 17:41.810
Are you still sure you wanna
bet it all on beating Boston?

17:43.896 --> 17:46.565
-How's your mother?
-She's pretending to be asleep.

17:46.648 --> 17:48.942
Landed on my best hotel
and conked right out.

17:49.026 --> 17:51.487
A Monopoly man, huh?

17:51.570 --> 17:53.363
Yeah. You play?

17:53.447 --> 17:55.032
I used to when
the kids were young.

17:55.115 --> 17:57.409
And then, they decided
to stop playing with me

17:57.493 --> 17:59.787
because I guess I can be
a little competitive.

17:59.870 --> 18:01.497
-Mine started ganging up

18:01.580 --> 18:04.124
together with their mother
to beat me.

18:04.208 --> 18:06.001
I'd be out making
business deals all week.

18:06.085 --> 18:08.045
They'd be plotting how
to keep me off of Boardwalk.

18:08.128 --> 18:10.005
You know, I probably should've
let 'em win more often.

18:10.088 --> 18:11.965
Maybe we'd still be playing.

18:16.345 --> 18:18.013
You always think
there's gonna be a point

18:18.096 --> 18:19.598
where it's gonna
slow down, don't you?

18:22.059 --> 18:25.729
Now, we got two in college,
two more about to be in college.

18:25.813 --> 18:28.357
-And here's your vacation.

18:28.440 --> 18:30.651
Wanna play a game?

18:30.734 --> 18:32.820
If you think you can handle it.

18:32.903 --> 18:35.823
You don't strike me as
somebody who likes to lose.

18:35.906 --> 18:38.283
Oh, the top hat never loses.

18:38.367 --> 18:41.370
Not until he gets his ass
kicked by the shoe.

18:42.246 --> 18:43.831
Really?

18:44.915 --> 18:46.375
Clear off the Jell-O, hotshot.

18:46.458 --> 18:49.169
You're about to taste
the wrath of the top hat.

18:56.802 --> 18:59.555
Anchorman
Local Lansing hero
Earvin "Magic" Johnson

18:59.638 --> 19:02.724
is back in Michigan tonight,
and not just on your TVs,

19:02.808 --> 19:04.726
advertising shoes.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.436
Of course, with all

19:06.520 --> 19:09.356
the fancy shit our boy's
been up to in LA,

19:09.439 --> 19:12.693
the question on everybody's
mind, will Magic bother

19:12.776 --> 19:16.488
looking twice at his old
homegirl Cookie Kelly?

19:16.572 --> 19:18.699
Or did he only send
her tickets to the game

19:18.782 --> 19:21.535
to rub her nose in it
that he's moved on,

19:21.618 --> 19:25.539
and she's a head case for
still carrying the torch?

19:25.622 --> 19:27.332
-Tune in--

19:27.416 --> 19:29.501
Girl, when you are married,

19:29.585 --> 19:31.962
you buying me a big old
diamond ring to match

19:32.045 --> 19:34.923
-for introducing you.
A finder's fee.

19:35.007 --> 19:37.885
Honestly,
I don't even think
I'm interested.

19:39.469 --> 19:41.305
So, you ain't worried?

19:41.388 --> 19:42.264
Mm-mmm!

19:42.347 --> 19:43.599
Boy always had a wandering eye.

19:43.682 --> 19:45.267
Bet by now,
they fell right out his head,

19:45.350 --> 19:47.436
Then why he calling me then?

19:47.519 --> 19:48.937
Every night, out there in Cali.

19:49.021 --> 19:51.064
Why'd he send
the last girl's daddy

19:51.148 --> 19:53.025
just so I would
show my face?

19:53.108 --> 19:55.903
Girl, I don't need no ring.

19:55.986 --> 19:59.072
I got that man wrapped
around my little finger.

19:59.156 --> 20:00.407
Okay, Cookie.

20:08.707 --> 20:10.250
-Over here!
-Yeah, it's good to be back.

20:10.334 --> 20:12.961
-Real good. Yeah. There you go.

20:16.381 --> 20:18.467
Yeah, no problem.
What's your name? Shawn?

20:18.550 --> 20:19.968
My name is Shawn.
It's nice to meet you!

20:20.052 --> 20:21.136
Hey, Shawn.

20:21.219 --> 20:23.639
Man, I got you.
Here you go.

20:23.722 --> 20:24.723
Thanks, man!

20:24.806 --> 20:27.184
Well, isn't he
the center of attention?

20:27.267 --> 20:29.353
Yeah yeah, he sure is.

20:29.436 --> 20:31.188
-You gonna be as good
as me one day.
-Thank you so much!

20:31.271 --> 20:33.190
-So cool.
-You're the best, Magic!

20:33.273 --> 20:36.234
I'm sorry, y'all.
I gotta go. Cook!

20:37.069 --> 20:40.238
Mm-mmm!

20:40.322 --> 20:43.116
You believe this?
Since we rode in.

20:43.200 --> 20:45.953
-Thought Stevie Wonder
must be in town, but no!

20:46.036 --> 20:47.537
It's all for me.

20:49.915 --> 20:52.125
It's... something else.

20:52.209 --> 20:53.377
Ain't it?

20:55.253 --> 20:56.463
Hey, Rhonda.

20:56.546 --> 20:57.673
Hey.

20:57.756 --> 20:59.424
I missed you.

21:00.175 --> 21:01.510
Mm, stop.

21:01.593 --> 21:04.262
You stop lookin'
so good.

21:04.346 --> 21:06.598
Earleatha, darling,
you look ravishing!

21:06.682 --> 21:07.975
Dr. Day.

21:08.058 --> 21:10.185
Man from Buick
is here to see you.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.062
Oh, can it wait?

21:12.145 --> 21:13.647
Gonna see Pop
later on tonight,

21:13.730 --> 21:15.315
he was wanting
to talk it over.

21:15.399 --> 21:18.902
Best not. Bad idea to
keep these corporations waiting.

21:18.986 --> 21:21.196
Look-it, you want to get
the old man on the phone?

21:27.327 --> 21:30.664
Nah. Nah. You think
it's the real deal,

21:30.747 --> 21:32.332
-let's do it.
-Okay. Wise man.

21:32.416 --> 21:34.960
Excuse us for a minute, angels.

21:36.294 --> 21:38.463
I'll be right back, Cook.
-Mm-hm.

21:38.547 --> 21:41.675
I heard he picks some girls
out of the stands at every game.

21:41.758 --> 21:44.428
You should've worn
a brighter color.

21:44.511 --> 21:47.222
You could've wore
a disco ball, bitch.

21:53.145 --> 21:54.896
Come on, Cookie.

22:06.616 --> 22:09.036
Coach Riley.
Coach Riley.

22:10.120 --> 22:11.663
I'm Coach Riley.

22:21.548 --> 22:23.216
How you doin'? Ahem.

22:25.886 --> 22:28.555
Jerry
What the fuck's this
motherfucker up to?

22:29.765 --> 22:32.267
Oh, wow. Hi. Hey, Jerry.

22:37.564 --> 22:40.901
-This Detroit?
-Yes, it is, Jerry. Hi.

22:40.984 --> 22:42.569
How's the scout coming?

22:42.652 --> 22:45.989
Uh-huh. Yeah, it's...
coming. Just, uh,

22:46.073 --> 22:49.242
just making sure we got
the personnel we need
to make a run.

22:54.498 --> 22:55.957
We're, uh...

22:57.000 --> 22:58.835
we're turning it around.

22:58.919 --> 23:00.754
Just you watch.

23:00.837 --> 23:02.214
Mm-hmm.

23:08.095 --> 23:10.180
Mm. Hey, Jer.

23:11.098 --> 23:12.849
Eating my leftovers?

23:15.936 --> 23:18.855
-I'll leave you boys to it.
-Alright.

23:20.148 --> 23:22.859
Lay off the fuckin'
French fries.

23:25.237 --> 23:26.863
I like french fries.

23:26.947 --> 23:29.533
Don't sweat it, alright?
Come on. He's a busybody.

23:30.492 --> 23:32.619
Don't sweat it.
Anyway...

23:33.453 --> 23:35.497
God's smiling. Hm?

23:37.582 --> 23:39.543
Detroit's the pits
of the league.

23:40.377 --> 23:41.920
We got these suckers.

23:42.003 --> 23:44.756
Well, folks, the Lakers are
looking to redeem themselves

23:44.840 --> 23:46.550
and move from
Santa's naughty list

23:46.633 --> 23:48.301
to something nicer
with a win tonight

23:48.385 --> 23:50.262
against the last place
Detroit Pistons.

23:50.345 --> 23:52.013
Shouldn't take
a Christmas miracle

23:52.097 --> 23:53.890
to mark this one a W.

24:12.701 --> 24:14.911
Sent the bus to Lansing.

24:14.995 --> 24:17.831
I told them you
had family in town.

24:17.914 --> 24:19.749
I'm certainly glad I don't.

24:19.833 --> 24:21.168
It's one game. Hm?

24:21.251 --> 24:23.962
Who watches basketball
on Christmas?

24:25.714 --> 24:27.465
Shake it off
and function forward.

24:27.549 --> 24:29.509
Forward where?

24:29.593 --> 24:32.387
You said yourself
we're in the fucking pits.

24:32.471 --> 24:35.056
We just got blown out by the
worst team in the league, so...

24:35.140 --> 24:36.766
Well, not anymore.

24:37.559 --> 24:38.977
They beat us.

24:39.060 --> 24:41.479
Alright, we're sitting
on a pile of coal.

24:41.563 --> 24:43.523
We put on our big boy pants,

24:43.607 --> 24:46.401
we put our heads together,
and we press out
a diamond in Boston.

24:46.484 --> 24:47.652
What's gonna change?

24:48.570 --> 24:50.155
Huh? Me?

24:51.489 --> 24:52.949
Pat...

24:53.033 --> 24:55.035
I'm not supposed to be here.

24:55.118 --> 24:57.746
It's Jack's team.
You're Jack's guy.

24:57.829 --> 25:00.624
And Jack's coming back,
right?

25:00.707 --> 25:02.334
Few more weeks.

25:06.755 --> 25:10.217
It's the dramatist in me.
You're right.

25:14.221 --> 25:17.390
Hey. You got plans
for Christmas? Huh?

25:17.474 --> 25:18.975
No.

25:19.059 --> 25:20.185
Yes, you do.

25:20.268 --> 25:21.645
Bringing in Chinese,

25:21.728 --> 25:23.230
we're drinking a six-pack,

25:23.313 --> 25:26.274
and we're figuring out how we're
going to ruin Boston's New Year.

25:26.358 --> 25:28.276
Huh?

25:28.360 --> 25:30.570
Yeah. Yeah. Alright.

25:30.654 --> 25:32.155
Fuck Boston.

25:41.915 --> 25:44.834
What that game was
is a lesson in humility.

25:44.918 --> 25:47.087
Showboating, fancy passes.

25:47.170 --> 25:48.505
No wonder you had
all those turnovers.

25:48.588 --> 25:50.465
Ma, you wasn't even there.

25:50.548 --> 25:52.300
Christine
I know my son.

25:52.384 --> 25:55.720
She was listening on the radio.

25:55.804 --> 25:58.473
Every game.
And you better believe it.

25:58.556 --> 26:01.518
So, I might tune in on occasion.

26:01.601 --> 26:04.354
-Let me talk to you.

26:04.437 --> 26:07.107
Earvin Johnson Sr.:
We gotta talk about
that Buick deal.

26:07.190 --> 26:08.525
Been doing some research.

26:08.608 --> 26:10.902
Not sure you wanna put
your name on them cars, son.

26:10.986 --> 26:14.823
Boys on the line been saying
quality is falling off.

26:16.700 --> 26:19.077
Look, Pop, uh, thing is...

26:19.160 --> 26:22.163
I actually already
signed the deal today.

26:22.247 --> 26:25.083
Dr. Day got it worked out
real good though.

26:25.166 --> 26:27.377
He did, huh?

26:27.460 --> 26:30.171
Told you he was
helping me, didn't I?

26:30.255 --> 26:33.049
-Yeah, you mentioned that.
-Dr. There's
the man of the hour.

26:33.133 --> 26:36.886
And... the man's old man.

26:36.970 --> 26:39.014
How you doin' there,
brother Earvin?

26:39.097 --> 26:41.683
You still
workin' the line?

26:41.766 --> 26:44.269
Honest pay
for an honest day.

26:44.352 --> 26:45.979
How's your daughter
doing though?

26:46.062 --> 26:47.314
-Hm?
-Dr. Oh.

26:47.397 --> 26:50.734
-She be blessed
and highly favored.
-Pop...

26:50.817 --> 26:53.903
-Blessed on her knees.
-Hey, Pop, Pop, Pop.

26:53.987 --> 26:56.489
Why don't you let us
talk some business?

26:56.573 --> 26:58.491
I thought that's
what we do together.

26:58.575 --> 27:01.202
Dr. Day been doing right by me!

27:01.286 --> 27:04.331
We building
Magic Johnson Enterprises.

27:05.457 --> 27:09.044
It's not Magic Johnson
on my mind.

27:09.127 --> 27:11.629
You got a lot of people
in your ear, son.

27:11.713 --> 27:14.799
Ain't many of them family.
You hear me?

27:14.883 --> 27:15.967
Yeah.

27:16.551 --> 27:17.552
Yeah.

27:19.804 --> 27:20.805
Johnson Sr.: Hm?

27:21.473 --> 27:22.891
I hear you, Pop.

27:22.974 --> 27:25.727
I got this though.

27:25.810 --> 27:29.272
You gonna have the window
office right next to mine.

27:29.356 --> 27:31.107
Go get some of Mama's pie
or something, man.

27:31.191 --> 27:33.818
Stop talking
so much business.

27:33.902 --> 27:35.904
I didn't make the world.
I'm just saying the way it is,

27:35.987 --> 27:38.990
and Boston? Look, that...

27:39.074 --> 27:41.034
That fuckin' place
is worse than anywhere.

27:41.117 --> 27:44.454
Bill Russell won
the motherfuckers...

27:45.622 --> 27:47.207
11 rings!

27:47.290 --> 27:49.751
Comes home to his abode
to find the door open.

27:49.834 --> 27:51.419
They didn't even
have the decency

27:51.503 --> 27:54.255
to burn a cross
on this man's lawn.

27:54.339 --> 27:57.133
Just shit in his bed.
Not dog shit neither.

27:57.217 --> 27:58.885
Man shit.

27:58.968 --> 28:00.303
Yeah...

28:00.387 --> 28:02.639
different kinda
white people over there.

28:02.722 --> 28:04.516
See, Boston Garden,

28:04.599 --> 28:07.977
brothers walk into that place
and you can feel it

28:08.061 --> 28:09.979
like a cold wind.

28:10.063 --> 28:12.941
You find yourself
running down the court,

28:13.024 --> 28:15.276
tripping over thin air.
Go to dribble,

28:15.360 --> 28:17.904
ball don't bounce.
Just sticks there.

28:17.987 --> 28:20.240
Like a mud puddle.

28:20.323 --> 28:23.618
No logical explanation
to it neither. But then,

28:23.701 --> 28:25.954
you hear something.

28:26.037 --> 28:28.164
-Like a little giggle.

28:28.248 --> 28:29.999
Take that, nigga!

28:32.627 --> 28:33.711
And it ain't ghosts.

28:33.795 --> 28:35.463
It's a leprechaun.

28:35.547 --> 28:38.800
I believe it.
I definitely believe it.

28:38.883 --> 28:40.552
Dr.
Look at this
Buick contract here.

28:40.635 --> 28:42.554
See your name.
That's number one.

28:42.637 --> 28:44.180
-Mm-hmm.
-Your likeness?

28:44.264 --> 28:46.808
-Mm-hmm.
-Let's go right here.
See that right there?

28:46.891 --> 28:49.769
-Mm-hmm!
-Television. Commercial.

28:49.853 --> 28:52.188
United States and Europe.

28:52.272 --> 28:54.649
-International, boy.

28:54.732 --> 28:58.278
-You international.
That's international, boy!
-Yeah!

28:58.361 --> 28:59.779
Dr.
Hold on, wait a minute.

28:59.863 --> 29:02.449
-Whoo! Yeah.
-We didn't get to
the best part yet.

29:03.533 --> 29:04.993
Dr.
Ain't nobody makin'

29:05.076 --> 29:06.536
one more second...

29:06.619 --> 29:07.871
-that kinda money.
-Whoo!

29:07.954 --> 29:09.289
Big fella,

29:09.372 --> 29:11.040
let me know if you want seconds.

29:11.124 --> 29:12.625
These are thirds.

29:12.709 --> 29:15.295
What I need now is a recipe

29:15.378 --> 29:18.006
-before I eat you
out of house and home.
-Earvin Sr.: Please.

29:18.089 --> 29:21.342
The great Kareem Abdul-Jabbar?

29:21.426 --> 29:23.386
More than welcome to it.

29:23.470 --> 29:26.473
Still smile to think of
my own son passing the ball

29:26.556 --> 29:29.517
to the greatest center
ever played the game.

29:29.601 --> 29:32.979
-No need for that.
-Hey. Truth is truth.

29:33.771 --> 29:35.064
He's not so bad himself.

29:36.441 --> 29:38.568
-No...
-What up!

29:38.651 --> 29:40.487
I guess he ain't.

29:40.570 --> 29:42.947
Can I ask you a question,
Mr. Johnson?

29:43.031 --> 29:45.116
-Merry Christmas!
-Oh, yeah, here he is!

29:45.200 --> 29:46.326
Y'all enjoyin'
y'all selves?

29:46.409 --> 29:48.620
You can if you can cut
that Mr. Johnson crap

29:48.703 --> 29:50.830
and just call me Earvin.

29:52.081 --> 29:55.710
Your son.
Has he always been so...

29:57.545 --> 29:58.546
happy?

29:58.630 --> 30:00.715
Mm! Mm! Hey!

30:00.798 --> 30:02.759
Junior?

30:03.635 --> 30:06.095
Only since his first breath.

30:07.138 --> 30:09.390
Doctor slapped his ass,

30:09.474 --> 30:12.101
he turned around
and smiled back.

30:12.185 --> 30:13.311
Hey! You heard?

30:13.394 --> 30:15.605
-I can imagine.
-Earvin Sr.: Yeah.

30:17.732 --> 30:19.609
Something on your chest,
Mr. Jabbar?

30:19.692 --> 30:21.027
Kareem.

30:21.736 --> 30:23.279
Kareem.

30:23.363 --> 30:25.698
I just can't say
I'm accustomed to it.

30:25.782 --> 30:28.743
Most men I know,
Black men,

30:29.452 --> 30:31.204
we laugh,

30:31.287 --> 30:34.749
enjoy our lives.
But, America does...

30:34.832 --> 30:37.460
things to
a man's mind and soul

30:37.544 --> 30:39.254
that aren't happy.

30:41.714 --> 30:44.926
Pardon my saying it,
but your son...

30:46.094 --> 30:49.305
-seems unaffected by all that.
-Mm.

30:49.389 --> 30:51.891
'Cause he is.

30:51.975 --> 30:54.269
-How?
-Wish I knew.

30:54.352 --> 30:56.938
I'm from Mississippi.

30:57.021 --> 30:59.732
Down there, we're gator bait.

30:59.816 --> 31:03.236
Wasn't a week went by when
I was young ain't seen some...

31:10.285 --> 31:13.705
-Then you know.
-Too well. But he don't.

31:17.375 --> 31:18.918
Not like that.

31:19.002 --> 31:20.587
And it

31:20.670 --> 31:24.716
feels like we ain't speaking
the same tongue sometimes but...

31:26.384 --> 31:29.971
then I think, hey,
maybe that's a blessing, too.

31:31.556 --> 31:34.100
When it don't scare me shitless.

31:36.603 --> 31:38.605
I'll whoop his ass
if he gets out of line.

31:38.688 --> 31:41.566
